            <h2 class="white-word">What is an indigenous plant?</h2>
            <p class="white-word">
                Native plants are plants that grow in a particular country like Australia. Indigenous plants are native to Australia, most importantly they are natural to your local area.
            </p>
            <h2 class="white-word">Why plant indigenous plants?</h2>
            <p class="white-word">
                In recent years, our indigenous plants have been removed or outcompeted by exotic plants. Indigenous plants were and continue to be an important food source for our local wildlife. They are great to have because they are perfectly suited to the environment that they belong to. This means that they should survive on local weather and thrive in the local soil.
            </p>
            <h2 class="white-word">Indigenous plants also:</h2>
            <ul class="white-word">
                <li>provide habitat, shelter, and food for local wildlife.</li>
                <li>require less water and money.</li>
                <li>support a healthy environment.</li>
                <li>improve biodiversity.</li>
                <li>are our heritage – we can help preserve them.</li>
                <li>are attractive plants with less maintenance. </li>
                <li>get less plant disease and more pest resistance.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
